column1: If you use data presented in this website, we ask you to add a reference to your publication in the following recommended format:

Stuefer S.L. and Youcha, E.K., [year of retrieval], Hydrology of Imnavait Creek and Kuparuk River in Alaska. University of Alaska Fairbanks, Water and Environmental Research Center. [URL]. Accessed [month, day and year of retrieval].
Note: 6999 denotes missing or invalid data and 7777 denotes uncollected data,
ICE indicates creek is affected by anchor, shelf, or floating ice during snowmelt runoff or late fall period, EST-estimated

Note: Manual discharge measurements are made during snowmelt runoff period and data are interpolated between measurements.  Historical WERC rating curve used once creek is ice-free. Shifts may be applied to rating curve due to weir adjustments or backwater issues at weir
